               <msContents>
                  <summary>Homiliary in Honor of the Archangel Michael, ድርሳነ፡ ሚካኤል፡</summary>
                  <textLang mainLang="gez">Gə‘əz</textLang>
               <msItem xml:id="ms_i1"><locus from = "1r" to = "88v"/><title type = "complete" ref = "LIT1295Dersan"/>
               <note>
               a. <locus from="1r" to="16v"/> Ḫədar.‎
               ‎(1) <locus from="1r" to="12v"/> Homily by Dämatewos. ‎
               ‎(2) <locus from="12v" to="14r"/> Miracle ‎
               ‎(3) <locus from="14r" to="16r"/> Synaxary entry: Mission of the Archangel to ‎Joshua, son of Nun.‎
               ‎(4) <locus from="16r" to="16v"/> Greeting to the Archangel, Sälam.‎
               b. <locus from="16v" to="23v"/> Taḥsas.‎
               ‎(1) <locus from="16v" to="22r"/> Homily of John the Archbishop.‎
               ‎(2) <locus from="22r" to="23r"/> Miracle.‎
               ‎(3) <locus from="23r" to="23v"/> Synaxary Entry: Mission of the Archangel to ‎rescue the three holy children.‎
               ‎(4) <locus from="23v"/> Greeting to the Archangel, Sälam.‎
               c. <locus from="23v" to="29r"/> Ṭərr
               ‎(1) <locus from="23v" to="28r"/> Homily, author not given. ‎
               ‎(2) <locus from="28r" to="28v"/> Miracle.‎
               ‎(3) <locus from="28v" to="29r"/> Synaxary Entry: Mission of the Archangel to ‎save Jacob from the wrath of Esau.‎
               ‎(4) <locus from="29r"/> Greeting to the Archangel, Sälam.‎
               d. <locus from="29r" to="33v"/> Yäkkatit.‎
               ‎(1) <locus from="29r" to="32r"/> Homily, author not given.‎
               ‎(2) <locus from="32r" to="33r"/> Miracle.‎
               ‎(3) <locus from="33r" to="33v"/> Synaxary Entry: Mission of the Archangel to ‎Samson, the giant.‎
               ‎(4) <locus from="33v"/> Greeting to the Archangel, Sälam.‎
               e. <locus from="33v" to="48r"/> Mäggabit.‎
               ‎(1) <locus from="33v" to="47r"/> Homily by the archbishop of Antioch.‎
               ‎(2) <locus from="47r" to="48r"/> Miracle.‎
               ‎(3) <locus from="48r"/> Synaxary Entry: Mission of the Archangel to ‎Balaam.‎
               ‎(4) <locus from="48r"/> Greeting to the Archangel, Sälam.‎
               <locus from="48v" to="55r"/> Miyazya.‎
               ‎(1) <locus from="48v" to="53r"/> Homily (attributed to Cyril) on the greatness or ‎glory of the Archangel Michael, cp. EMIP 16, <locus from="1r" to="4r"/>.‎
               ‎(2) <locus from="53r" to="54v"/> Miracle.‎
               ‎(3) <locus from="54v" to="55r"/> Synaxary entries: Mission of the Archangel to ‎the Prophet Jeremiah and Bishop Anthony.‎
               ‎(4) <locus from="55r"/> Greeting to the Archangel, Sälam.‎
               g. <locus from="55r" to="65r"/> Gənbot.‎
               ‎(1) <locus from="55r" to="63v"/> Homily by Yoḥannəs, Bishop of Ethiopia, who ‎came after Bishop Yəḥaq, on the conflict between the ‎consort of King Arqadewos and John Chrysostom.‎
               ‎(2) <locus from="63v" to="65r"/> Miracle.‎
               ‎     Synaxary entry and Greeting missing: ‎
               h. <locus from="65r" to="73v"/> Säne
               ‎     Homily and Miracle missing
               ‎(1) <locus from="65r" to="71r"/> Synaxary entry: The building of the church of ‎the Archangel in place of a pagan temple in Alexandria.‎
               ‎(2) <locus from="71r"/> Greeting to the Archangel, Sälam.‎
               ‎      (3) <locus from="71r"/> Synaxary entry for Saint Kristos Kǝbra.‎
               ‎      (4) <locus from="71r"/> Greeting to the Archangel, Sälam.‎
               ‎      (5) <locus from="71r" to="72v"/> Synaxary entry for Saint Afomya.‎
               ‎      (6) <locus from="72v" to="73r"/> Greeting to the Archangel, Sälam.‎
               ‎      (7) <locus from="73r"/> Synaxary entry for Gənbot: Mission of the ‎Archangel to Habakkuk.‎
               ‎      (8) <locus from="73r" to="73v"/> Greeting to the Archangel, Sälam.‎
               i. <locus from="73v" to="78v"/> Ḥamle
               ‎(1) <locus from="73v" to="77r"/> Homily (by Bishop Yoḥannəs) on the ‎wicked wealthy man whose property was inherited by ‎the son of his poor neighbor.‎
               ‎(2) <locus from="77r" to="78r"/> Miracle. ‎
               ‎(3) <locus from="78r" to="78v"/> Synaxary entry: Mission to the camp of ‎Sennacherib.‎
               ‎(4) <locus from="78v"/> Greeting to the Archangel, Sälam.‎
               j. <locus from="78v" to="82r"/> Näḥase
               ‎(1)  <locus from="78v" to="81r"/> Homily (anonymous) on the book of the ‎angels that came from Jerusalem.‎
               ‎(2) <locus from="81r" to="81v"/> Miracle. ‎
               ‎(3) <locus from="81v" to="82r"/> Synaxary entry: Mission of the Archangel to ‎the Emperor Constantine.‎
               ‎(4) <locus from="82r"/> Greeting to the Archangel, Sälam.‎
               k. <locus from="82r" to="85r"/> Mäskäräm.‎
               ‎(1) <locus from="82r" to="84v"/> Homily (anonymous) on not worshipping other ‎gods.‎
               ‎(2) <locus from="84v"/> Miracle, incomplete. Folio missing between <locus target="#84v #85r"/>.‎
               ‎(3) <locus from="85r"/> Synaxary entry, incomplete at the beginning: ‎Mission to Prophet Isaiah.‎
               ‎(4) <locus from="85r"/> Greeting to the Archangel, Sälam.‎
               l. <locus from="85r" to="88v"/> Ṭəqəmt.‎
               ‎(1) <locus from="85r" to="88r"/> Homily (anonymous) on the need to make the ‎angels sureties by honoring them.‎
               ‎(2) <locus from="88r" to="88v"/> Miracle, incomplete.‎
</note>
</msItem>
